txt.en: 'We have done good work here, and I am happy to be able to return home and get back to real work. The few Rangers I spoke with before they left were very cordial. They were excited about getting these relics back to Tinnudir but were also looking forward to a more open beneficial relationship with Ost Forod...something we will certainly welcome.\n\n'The Rangers told me Orchalwë at Tinnudir wanted to speak with you. I believe it is to thank you for your help and aid, but suspect there will be more to do.'

'The tomb-robbers will threaten our history no more. I thank you greatly for your work to stop them. I know we sent you initially to repair the pact with Ost Forod, but to have you -- and them -- go above and beyond and deliver us Rantost. Words cannot express my gratitude.'
'You should speak with Orchalwë at Tinnudir.'
The Rangers at Tinnudir will want to speak with you about Rantost, the tomb-robbers, and what comes next.
Orchalwë is at Tinnudir, south of Rantost.\n\nOrchalwë wants to speak with you about what is next for Evendim.
